special_type: He has a behavior goal and a communication goal so he receives behavior related special education and sees the school based speech pathologist.
school_problem_desc: We've had significant behavior issues with Solomon in school in the past. In April 2022, for example, we were called to the school multiple times in one week because his behaviors were out of control (throwing things in the classroom, melting down, or running away from the school)
school_problems_begin: We've had two bouts with it. Once in Kindergarten at the start of the year which lasted a few months and once at the end of 1st grade which lasted a few months.
illness_disability_desc: He has PFAPA. ADHD, and GAD. He was also diagnosed when he was younger with a mixed expressive-receptive language delay.
child_concerns: Solomon is a very black and white thinking and really struggles with grey areas. This sometimes causes him to feel like people are mocking him when their reactions have nothing to do with him. For example, we were laughing at something people said at our family Christmas and he kept asking, "what's so funny?!" in a frustrated tone. He doesn't quite understand why people find things funny and is very adamant about people explaining what made them laugh, smile, etc. Especially if he perceives it to be related to making fun of him.
child_best_quality: Solomon is such an incredible story teller. A couple of months ago he verbally made up a 3 chapter story (and it had an additional bonus chapter!). After he finished telling me the story (10-15 minutes of straight talking) he gave me a 10 question quiz that included true/false questions, multiple choice questions, fill in the blank questions, and inference questions. In case you're wondering- I got 50% on it, LOL! The other thing I love about Solomon is that he is so FUNNY. His laugh is literally the best sound I've heard in my entire life. He likes to make jokes (which aren't always funny) but his laughter makes up for it. He's also incredibly receptive to emotional conversations and does an excellent job with talking about his feelings after he's gotten upset. For example, he told me once after I got really upset and yelled at him and his brother that it's okay for me to be angry but it's not okay to scare people. Then he very sweetly told me that no one has to be perfect and that I should try better next time.
certain_thoughts: He's obsessed with story telling. There's a whole universe about this character Master Solomon that he's made up and if he can't have 2 or 3 minutes to get it out of his head he literally cannot go back to what he's doing without being upset.
nervous_mvmt: I don't know if it's nervousness but he does stim a lot. Moves hands, jumps in place while flapping his hands.
speech_problem_desc: It's not so much with his speech as it is with his understanding of complex how/why questions.
stores_things_desc: He likes to keep certain things out of reach of his brother, like in a zipped coat pocket, but he doesn't typically hoard anything. Aside from books in his bedroom.
